<mjml>
  <mj-head>
    <mj-attributes>
      <mj-button padding="0" />
      <mj-column padding="0" />
      <mj-image padding="0" />
      <mj-section padding="0 0 48px" />
      <mj-table padding="0" />
      <mj-text
        font-family="-apple-system, 'system-ui', 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif"
        font-size="14px"
        padding="0"
      />
      <mj-wrapper padding="0" />
    </mj-attributes>

    <mj-style>
      body {
        background-color: #ffffff;
        padding: 0 12px;
      }

      .logo {
        border: 0 solid #9e9e9e;
        border-width: 1px 0 0;
        color: #737373;
        font-size: 0;
        padding: 24px 0 12px;
        text-align: center;
      }
      .logo-title {
        font-size: 24px;
        margin: 0 auto 12px;
      }
      .logo-element {
        background-color: #9e9e9e;
        border: 1px solid #fff;
        box-sizing: border-box;
        display: inline-block;
        height: 12px;
        list-style: none;
        margin: 0 2px;
        padding: 0;
        vertical-align: top;
        width: 12px;
      }
      .tall {
        height: 24px;
        margin: 0 2px;
      }
      .wide {
        width: 24px;
      }
      .blue {
        background-color: #2196f3;
      }
      .blue-alt {
        background-color: #90caf9;
      }
      .orange {
        background-color: #ff9800;
      }
      .green {
        background-color: #8bc34a;
      }
      .green-alt {
        background-color: #b2ff59;
      }
      .dateline {
        font-size: 12px;
        margin: 12px auto;
        text-align: center;
      }

      .article {
        background-color: #f5f5f5;
        border-bottom: 1px solid #e0e0e0;
        border-radius: 4px 4px 0 0;
        padding: 0 !important;
      }

      .social-links {
        background-color: #f5f5f5;
        border: 0 solid #e0e0e0;
        border-width: 1px 0;
        margin: 0 !important;
        padding: 12px 0 !important;
        text-align: center;
      }
      .social-links a {
        margin: 0 12px;
      }
      .unsubscribe {
        cursor: pointer;
        font-size: 12px;
        margin:  12px 0 !important;
        text-align: right;
        text-decoration: underline;
      }
    </mj-style>

    <mj-style inline="inline">
      .web-version-link {
        color: #0071CE;
        margin: 12px 0;
        text-align: right;
      }

      h2 {
        border-bottom: 1px solid #e0e0e0;
        color: #616161;
        line-height: 1.25em;
        margin: 1.25rem 0 0;
        padding: 0 12px 1.25rem;
      }

      h3 {
        color: #616161;
        font-size: 16px;
        line-height: 1.25em;
        margin: 1.25rem 0;
        padding: 0 12px;
      }

      hr {
        border-top: 1px solid #e0e0e0;
        height: 0;
        margin: 1.25rem 12px;
      }

      p {
        color: #707070;
        line-height: 1.5em;
        margin: 1.125rem 0;
        padding: 0 12px;
      }

      a {
        color: #0071CE;
        cursor: pointer;
        font-weight: bold;
        text-decoration: underline;
      }

      dl {
        color: #707070;
        line-height: 1.5em;
        margin: 1.125rem 0;
        padding: 0 12px;
      }
      dt {
        font-size: 14px;
        font-weight: bold;
        margin: 1.125rem 0 0.625em;
      }
      dd {
        font-size: 13px;
        margin: 0.625rem 0;
      }

      figure {
        margin: 1.5rem 0;
      }

      h2 + figure {
        margin-top: 0;
      }

      img {
        display: block;
        height: auto;
        max-width: 100%;
      }

      svg {
        display: inline-block;
        height: 18px;
        margin-right: 4px;
        vertical-align: middle;
        width: 18px;
      }

      figcaption {
        color: #707070;
        font-size: 12px;
        line-height: 1.5em;
        margin: 6px 12px 0;
      }

      ol, ul {
        color: #707070;
        margin: 1.125rem 0;
        padding: 0 32px;
      }

      li {
        line-height: 1.125em;
        list-style: square;
        margin: 0.5rem 0;
      }
    </mj-style>

    <mj-title>The Turning Gate</mj-title>
  </mj-head>

  <mj-body>

    <mj-section padding-bottom="0">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text>
          <div class="web-version-link">
            <webversion>view web version</webversion>
          </div>

          <div class="logo">
            <h1 class="logo-title">The Turning Gate</h1>

            <span class="logo-element"></span>
            <span class="logo-element blue-alt"></span>
            <span class="logo-element wide blue"></span>
            <span class="logo-element tall wide orange"></span>
            <span class="logo-element"></span>
            <span class="logo-element"></span>
            <span class="logo-element"></span>
            <span class="logo-element tall green"></span>
            <span class="logo-element"></span>
            <span class="logo-element"></span>
            <span class="logo-element green-alt"></span>

            <div class="dateline">[currentmonth] [currentdaynumber], [currentyear]</div>
          </div>

        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>    

    <mj-section>
      <mj-column>
        <mj-image alt="Taipei, Taiwan; February 2023." src="https://github.com/mjcampagna/mjml/blob/main/newsletters/202311/Cheaper-Easier-Backlight-5-Hero.jpg?raw=true" />
        <mj-text css-class="article">
          <p>Hi [Name,fallback=Friend],</p>
          <p>We've got important updates for nearly all versions of Backlight, making it cheaper and easier to upgrade from older versions of Backlight, to the latest Backlight 5. And no, this isn't a Black Friday offer; the new discounts are permanent!</p>
          <p>For Backlight 5 users, our latest update adds a new presentation type to Kookaburra, the image carousel. More on this below.</p>
        </mj-text>        
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

    <mj-section>
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text css-class="article">
          <h2>Cheaper, easier upgrades to Backlight 5</h2>
          <p><strong>TL;DR</strong></p>
          <p>New updates are available for Backlight verisons 2, 3, 4 and 5. Install the latest version from the Backlight Modules page of your admin.</p>
          <p>After updating, the Backlight Modules page will give you the option to upgrade to Backlight 5 with a discount.</p>
          <p>Save $35 when upgrading from Backlight 4 to Backlight 5, or $15 when upgrading to Backlight 5 from Backlight versions 2 or 3.</p>

          <hr />

          <p>Now, here's the longer version.</p>

          <p>Updates are now availble for all all versions of Backlight, from version 2 onward. This brings major Backlight releases to the following version numbers:</p>
          <ul>
          <li>Backlight 2.0.15</li>
          <li>Backlight 3.2.2</li>
          <li>Backlight 4.1.4</li>
          <li>Backlight 5.3.4</li>
          </ul>
          <p>First step, install the latest update from the Backlight Modules page of your admin.</p>
          <p>Then, if a newer version of Backlight is available than currently installed, the admin will now display a message in the admin footer to tell you so.</p>
          <p>If a major upgrade is available to purchase, then the Backlight Modules page will display a banner, allowing you to see what's new, and allowing you to purchase the upgrade with discount automatically applied. You no longer need to get a discount code from us!</p>

          <p>Upgrading from Backlight 4 to Backlight 5, save $35. This is the same discount as before, except we had planned to expire it at the end of this year; instead, we are making the discount permanent.</p>

          <p>Upgrading to Backlight 5 from any older version, we are offering a new $15 discount.</p>

          <p>Click the "Upgrade now ..." button on your Backlight Modules page to purchase your discounted upgrade. Complete checkout, then return to the Backlight Modules page to install the upgrade. Easy!</p>

          <p>For users of Backlight 1, you may also use the $15 discount, though you will need to contact me for a code, as Backlight 1 does not have the Backlight Modules page, or automated updates feature (first introduced in Backlight 2).</p>

          <p>For more information, see our blog post, <a href="https://blog.theturninggate.net/2023/11/18/cheaper-easier-upgrades-to-backlight-5/">Cheaper, easier upgrades to Backlight 5</a>.
        </mj-text>        
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

    <mj-section>
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text css-class="article">
          <h2>New! Kookaburra carousels</h2>
          <p>Backlight version 5.3.4 introduces a new presentation type -- image carousel -- for Kookaburra!</p>
          <ul>
          <li>Configure carousels in your Kookaburra Page template.</li>
          <li>Use carousels in albums by selecting the "Carousel" presentation type in your Kookaburra Album template; OR ...</li>
          <li>Use carousels in Kookaburra essays by selecting "Carousel" as your presentaion in the essay builder.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>I've posted <a href="https://campagna.photography/sandbox/carousel/">a carousel demonstration here</a>.</p>
          <p>At present, Kookaburra's carousels are marked as <em>beta</em>; there will be at least one more major update to this feature coming later to flesh things out. Feedback is welcome in the meantime; please let me know how you get on with using the new carousels.</p>
          <p>Carousels are being introduced as a free, native feature in Kookaburra; in Pangolin, you would have needed the Galleria Add-on, or the Vegas Slideshow presentation type in the Theater Add-on.</p>
        </mj-text>        
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

    <mj-section>
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text css-class="article">
          <h2>I tried Glaze, so you don't have to.</h2>
          <p>I read about a tool called Nightshade, that purports to "poison" the massive image sets used to train AI image-generators, currently being developed at the University of Chicago. Nightshade is coming soon to their existing tool, Glaze, which disrupts the ability for AI image generators to scrape images and mimic a specific artist's personal style. So, I tried out Glaze, and wrote about it <a href="https://blog.theturninggate.net/2023/11/06/i-tried-glaze-so-you-dont-have-to/">on the blog</a>.</p>
        </mj-text>        
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

